rComments: He's very knowledgeable about the subject matter, but doesn't do a great job making it understandable for individuals who are not well-versed in psychology. The exams are difficult and often feature material not covered in lecture.
Knows his stuff, sometimes has hard time toning it down to understanding level. Tests are tough.

Nori was a great professor. He always made sure students understood topics, and if anyone ever had a question he never hesitated to go back over the topic. His powerpoints were seriously the best. I just didn't like how the online quizzes often asked questions which seemed to have 2 correct responses, when in fact only one was right.

Nori uses examples of his past clients when describing the mental disorders learned about in class and likes to show videos of the disorders.  An interesting class for majors and not too difficult.  If you attend class regularly, you won't need the textbook.
